### 🚫 Common Anti-Patterns

#### ❌ Direct Database Access in Routers
```typescript
// ❌ DON'T: Import database directly
import { db, transactions } from '@workspace/database/src/schema';

// ❌ DON'T: Write queries in routers
export const badRouter = createTRPCRouter({
  list: protectedProcedure.query(async ({ ctx }) => {
    return await db.select().from(transactions); // ❌ Violates SoC
  }),
});
```

#### ❌ Inconsistent Query Options
```typescript
// ❌ DON'T: Use different patterns for server/client
// Server side
prefetch(trpc.transactions.list.queryOptions({ page: 1 }));

// Client side - inconsistent!
const { data } = trpc.transactions.list.useQuery({ page: 1 }); // ❌ Different pattern
```

#### ❌ Missing Error Boundaries
```typescript
// ❌ DON'T: Forget error handling
const { data } = useSuspenseQuery(queryOptions); // ❌ No error boundary
```

