### 📝 Summary Checklist

#### Server Setup
- ✅ Use `createTRPCContext` with Supabase auth
- ✅ Define `protectedProcedure` for authenticated routes  
- ✅ Compose routers in `_app.ts`
- ✅ Set up API route handler at `/api/trpc/[trpc]`

#### Client Setup  
- ✅ Wrap app with `TRPCReactProvider` in root layout
- ✅ Use `useTRPC()` hook in client components
- ✅ Follow `queryOptions` pattern for consistency

#### Database Integration
- ✅ Import query functions from `@workspace/database`
- ❌ Never import `db` instance or schemas in routers
- ✅ Use `TransactionFilters` and other exported types

#### Performance
- ✅ Prefetch on server with `HydrateClient`
- ✅ Use `useMemo` for stable query options
- ✅ Implement conditional polling for real-time updates
- ✅ Include pagination metadata

#### Error Handling
- ✅ Use `TRPCError` with appropriate codes
- ✅ Handle `TRPCClientError` in mutations
- ✅ Provide fallback states and error boundaries

Follow these patterns to maintain consistency and type safety across the Knitly monorepo.